The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Windfall for U-22 players
                                                   Windfall for U-22 players
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The IPL franchisees must have a minimum of 16 players per squad and will additionally comprise a minimum of four under-22 players, according to a statement issued by the League.         
	The squad of 16 will consist of a maximum of eight currently available foreign players. Each franchisee can have four foreign players in the playing XI.         
	The squad will comprise a minimum of four under-22 players (the catchment players and the Indian national players can be counted for this purpose.)         
	The minimum salary for under-22 players is $20,000 per year. For other Ranji and non-auction players, it is $50,000 per year, according to the release.         
	It is learnt that Bengal batsmen Debabrata Das, Arindam Ghosh may get the nod for the Calcutta team.         
	The catchment areas are defined by reference to a players registration with his local cricket association.         
	It is as follows:         
	 Bangalore  Karnataka, Goa and Services         
	 Calcutta  Bengal, Jharkhand, Assam, Tripura and Sikkim         
	 Chennai  Tamil Nadu, Kerala and Railways         
	 Delhi  Delhi, Uttar Pradesh and Madhya Pradesh         
	 Jaipur  Rajasthan, Gujarat, Baroda and Saurashtra.         
	 Hyderabad  Hyderabad, Andhra and Orissa         
	 Mohali  Haryana, Punjab, Himachal and J amp;K         
	 Mumbai  Mumbai, Maharashtra and Vidarbha                                                                                                                       
